Jonče Hristovski (Macedonian: Јонче Христовски; born 1931 in Bitola – 5 April 2000 in Skopje) was a Macedonian singer and composer of folk music.
Jonče Hristovski (Macedonian: Јонче Христовски; born 1931 in Bitola – 5 April 2000 in Skopje) was a Macedonian singer and composer of folk music.
Among his many successes, his most popular song is Makedonsko Devojče composed in 1964.
Jonče Hristovski suffered a terrible tragedy when his wife passed after giving birth to their twin daughters, Olgica and Nevenka.
